============================================================== Swagger ================================================================

Swagger Documentation

This is used for Documentation 
			-This swagger containes all the endpoints of RestAPIs.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Steps to Implement Swagger---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

1-add 2 depepndency of swagger 
	<!--springfox-swagger-ui-->
	<dependency>
		<groupId>io.springfox</groupId>
		<artifactId>springfox-swagger-ui</articfactId>
		<version>2.9.2</version>
	</dependency>
	

	<!--swagger 2-->
	<dependency>
		<groupId>io.springfox</groupId>
		<artifactId>springfox-swagger2</articfactId>
		<version>2.9.2</version>
	</dependency>

	
2-createa package named swagger and class as swaggerConfig

	import static springfac.documentation.builder.PathSelectors.regex;

	@Configuration
	@EnableSwagger2
	public class SwaggerConfig{

	@Bean //Docket is a Builder which is intended to be primary interface into swagger -spring mvc framework , this will create an UI
	public Docker ProductApi(){
			//
			//path of base package is the name of the package all the way down to controllers location
	return Docket(DocumentationType.SWAGGER_2).select().apis(RequestHandlerSelectors.basePackage("com.stackroute.SpringrestapiusingmongoDb.controller"))
	.paths(regex("/api/v2/.*")).build();//matching controller paths of theat service(regex ' . ' means "all/anything that is present" in regex ) 
	}//end of function			
	}//end of class

3-you can see a documentation is generated
4-head on to http://localhost:8083/v2/api-docs since its not in a readable format 
	
	http://localhost:8083/swagger-ui.html and play with swag on swagger 

5- you can enter the data and test your end points here also 
6- API Gateway cannot process the swagger for its a router ::-NOTE THIS 




sudo docker run -it --rm --name rabbitmq -p 5672:5672 -p 15672:15672 rabbitmq:3.8.23-management































































